  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install libmng by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sed -i "s:#include &lt;jpeg:#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;\n&amp;:" libmng_types.h &amp;&amp;
./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --disable-static &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <command>sed -i "..." libmng_types.h</command>: This command adds a
        missing header which would cause other apps that link to this package
        fail to compile.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

